{"type":"message","id":"07ada109","parentId":"ac787f21","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:15:05.406Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to think globally about the framework - not just a list of fixes, but a holistic assessment of what's really going on and what the big picture priorities should be.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully:\n\n1. **What is this system actually trying to do?** - It's a personal AI assistant built on OpenClaw with added layers: task orchestration, memory management, self-improvement, proactivity.\n\n2. **What's the core tension?** - The user's workspace shows a LOT of installed skills and infrastructure, but many are not actually running in a closed loop. There's a gap between \"installed\" and \"working\". The bootstrap断层 issue is a symptom of something deeper - the system doesn't have proper self-observability.\n   \n3. **The real problem is that skills are installed but not integrated** - memory-keeper, self-improving, proactivity, and task_orchestrator are all there, but they're not connected. The system has good individual components but no proper message bus or event system to tie them together, so they don't actually trigger each other.\n\n4. **There's a fundamental architecture issue with how memory works** - Session context lives in session storage, but there are multiple ways to store information (daily logs, entities, entity-archive, preferences), and the bootstrap mechanism fails silently without proper error handling, so memory doesn't survive across sessions reliably.\n\n5. **The skill system is fragile** - The workspace has accumulated many skills from experimentation, some of which have been deleted or are outdated, but the documentation doesn't clearly show which ones are actually active versus deprecated.\n\n6. **The core infrastructure is underbuilt** - There's no observability to understand what's happening, no circuit breakers for failure isolation, no automated recovery when things break, and no way to safely iterate on the system itself. The user ends up manually maintaining what should be automated.\n\n7. **The approach is too broad** - I need to focus on what actually matters: making the system self-aware enough to detect its own failures, ensuring it can recover gracefully, and building in proper feedback loops so the system learns rather than just accumulating features.\n\n8. **The real architectural problem** - These skills are just a collection of utilities, not a coherent system. The memory layer especially is fragmented with no unified schema or strategy, just ad-hoc files piling up. This needs a complete redesign.","thinkingSignature":"2db4895bcdb1f799e1646dc9acc736d73c0a83873c8275e8cfa668e4e853bb20"},{"type":"text","text":"好，深想一层。\n\n---\n\n### 这框架真正的问题是什么\n\n不是\"缺什么技能\"，是**有结构无闭环**。\n\n你在过去几个月装了一堆东西：task_orchestrator、self-improving、proactivity、memory-keeper、v8_scorer、v8_classifier……每一样单独看都有道理，但拼在一起之后：\n\n**没有任何一个技能在真正自动触发另一个技能。**\n\n- corrections.md 写了，没人读\n- memory-keeper 装了，没人调用\n- task_orchestrator 的 hooks 存在，没人接上\n- 80+ 实体归档积累了，没人整理\n\n这就是问题。**碎片越积越多，系统没有自我整理的能力。**\n\n---\n\n### 真正的根因\n\n两层缺失：\n\n**第一层：没有自我观测**\n\n系统不知道自己\"现在在干什么\"。没有运行日志、没有健康检查、没有异常告警。3104/3103 挂了没人知道，Bootstrap 断了没人发现，corrections 积攒了没人处理。\n\n**第二层：没有自我修复**\n\n发现了问题也没有自动修复手段。能力有，但都等着人手动触发。\n\n---\n\n### 全局优先级重新排\n\n| 优先级 | 做什么 | 为什么 |\n|--------|--------|--------|\n| **P0** | 让系统能感知自己 | 不知道状态就什么都做不了 |\n| **P0** | 建反馈闭环 | corrections → 行为更新，这条路必须通 |\n| **P1** | 整理记忆层 | 80+归档是负债，不是资产 |\n| **P1** | 清理过时技能 | SKILLS.md 和实际不符，会把人搞晕 |\n| **P2** | 备份机制 | workspace 损坏了没有回撤 |\n| **P2** | 降级预案 | 全挂时的保底方案 |\n| **P3** | 多 Agent 编排 | 没需求，先不动 |\n| **P3** | LLM Wiki 质量控制 | 等记忆层整理完再说 |\n\n---\n\n### 核心建议：三件事\n\n**① 建观测层**\n```\ncrontab 每5分钟检查：\n- 3101/3102/3103/3104 是否还活着\n- memory/ 今天有没有新文件\n- corrections.md 有没有未处理条目\n→ 异常时写入 heartbeat-failure.md 并告警\n```\n\n**② 打通 corrections 闭环**\n```\n规则：每次 heartbeat 时：\n  if corrections.md 有新条目：\n    → 自动读取新条目\n    → 更新对应 skill 的 SKILL.md\n    → 标记为\"已处理\"\n    → 记录到 log.md\n```\n\n**③ 记忆层重构**\n```\n停止往 entities-archive/ 塞东西\n改用：memory/entities/ 下每条记录带 last_reviewed 字段\n每月跑一次：删除 last_reviewed > 90 天的页面\n```\n\n---\n\n### 最后说一句\n\n你现在这套系统像一个**能力很强的个体，但没有养成自我反思的习惯**。技能装了很多，但没有形成\"做→检查→修正→进化\"的循环。\n\n第一件事：给我一个能自动跑的观测循环。其他的排队来。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":1114,"cacheRead":85730,"cacheWrite":86,"totalTokens":86984,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0013368,"cacheRead":0.0051438,"cacheWrite":0.00003225,"total":0.00652905}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776021276248,"responseId":"062b221b5036f472a4c94e8416bb8aa8"}}
