{"type":"message","id":"1994506f","parentId":"4f42e498","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:20:36.060Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The node process as root (PID 316790) isn't showing up anymore - maybe it exited or I'm not seeing it. Let me look at what's actually running more carefully.\n\nBut wait - the root 310 snapfuse processes are just snapd stuff, not the thing I was looking for. Let me re-examine.\n\nThe crontab shows a node process that runs on @reboot: `/home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/bin/node /home/ai/openclaw-router/openclaw-router.js`. Let me check if this is the one that crashed or if there's something else.\n\nActually, let me step back and think about what I've found:1. **OpenClaw Gateway** (PID 299583, node) - port 18789, 3102\n\n\n2. **Context API** (PID 432, node) - port 3101\n3. **Scoring service** (PID 599, node) - port 3103\n4. **Scene Classifier API** (PID 299508, python) - port 3104, using FastAPI with ML pipeline and rule-based fallback\n5. **OpenClaw Router** (@reboot, node) - separate routing infrastructure\n6. **Cron**: weather_report.sh daily at 8am, rule-tuner.js Sundays at 2am, and strategy-analyzer.js (part of the v8 system)\n\nThere's also the v8 system running with its own src/ directory containing context, executor, router, scheduler, scoring, security, observability, and skills modules, plus logs for the router, context, scoring, and v8 system itself.\n\nNow I'm realizing the Router process that should be running from the @reboot cron entry isn't actually showing up in the process list - it's either crashed or the process ID changed. The node process on port 3103 (PID 599) might actually be the Router instead of the scoring service, so I need to verify what's actually running versus what should be running. I need to dig into the v8 subsystem more carefully - it's not just logs, there's an entire scoring engine there. Let me also check what's actually running versus what the crontab says should be running, and focus on the workspace_backup I spotted since it might contain stale content that's affecting the current setup.","thinkingSignature":"f4b2d8660c88e7c4da4b53b6b53e1202c8174ca72568eee80db72a86fe782444"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hxcxmzxo3k7f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep -v grep | grep \"node.*openclaw\\|node.*router\\|node.*scoring\" | grep -v nvm"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hxcxmzxo3k7f_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/openclaw-router/openclaw-router.js | head -40"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79608,"output":566,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98211,"cost":{"input":0.023882399999999998,"output":0.0006791999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.025643819999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776021626247,"responseId":"062b23792dfddae3594c7d288be8883b"}}
