{"type":"message","id":"16348ac4","parentId":"a0d952f3","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:35:04.019Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to integrate the LLM Wiki entity page auto-generation system into the main OpenClaw framework. Let me think about how this could be done properly.\n\nThe current framework has:\n1. OpenClaw Gateway with hooks (auto-score-classify enabled but broken)\n2. v8 scoring engine (3103) - empty idle\n3. Scene classifier (3104) - returning 500 errors\n4. openclaw-router - dead due to dotenv\n5. memory-keeper.sh - exists but not in cron\n6. wiki-auto-learn.py - exists but not in cron\n\nThe LLM Wiki system is a Python-based auto-learning framework that:\n\n\n- Scans skills/ and docs/ for new content\n- Uses the LLM to generate/update entity pages\n- Runs lint checks and updates cross-references\n\nNow I'm thinking about three approaches to integrate this. The first would be hooking it into the session lifecycle as a post-response action that triggers the wiki-auto-learn cycle. The second would be making it a cron job that runs periodically and ingests new skills into the wiki. The third would be running it as a skill that gets called on-demand. The cron approach seems cleanest since it's already a periodic process in the OpenClaw framework.\n\nBut looking deeper, the real issue is that the v8 systems are sitting idle—they're not actually being invoked by the hooks even though they're available. So the most robust approach would be to fix the scene-classifier, then set up a cron job for wiki-auto-learn, and ensure the self-improvement loop connects back to entity page updates. Let me examine the actual integration points.","thinkingSignature":"4e3bfb8e336910982fc54d599864f665fa85cba84309d3be04e67de280ef53e9"},{"type":"text","text":"能。但不是塞进去，是**对齐接口**。\n\n---\n\n### 融合的关键障碍\n\n```\n现有 OpenClaw 框架有:\n├── v8 scoring engine (3103)  ← 等待任务\n├── scene classifier (3104)  ← 坏了\n└── hooks 系统               ← 想触发自动行为\n\nwiki-auto-learn 有:\n├── 扫描 → 分析 → 写实体页\n├── Lint 检查\n└── 纯 Python，无 API 接口\n```\n\n两者之间没有连接通道。\n\n---\n\n### 融合方案\n\n**目标：让 entity page 生成变成 OpenClaw 的一个可调用 Skill，同时支持 cron 自动化。**\n\n**方案：在 task_orchestrator skill 里加一个 `ingest` action**\n\n```\n用户: \"学一下这个项目\"\n    ↓\nv8 classifier 识别为 task_multi_step\n    ↓\nv8 scorer 打分 → SPAWN_SUBAGENT\n    ↓\n子 agent 调用 wiki_ingest skill\n    ↓\n扫描 skills/docs → LLM 分析 → 写 entity 页\n    ↓\n更新 entities/ 并写 log.md\n```\n\n**或者更简单——直接加 cron：**\n\n```\n# 每小时跑一次增量 ingest\n0 * * * * cd /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace && python3 scripts/wiki-auto-learn.py --mode=ingest --limit=5 >> logs/wiki-ingest.log 2>&1\n```\n\n---\n\n### 我建议先做哪件\n\n**第一优先级：给 wiki-auto-learn.py 加 API 接口，让 task_orchestrator 能调用它**\n\n需要：\n1. 给 `wiki-auto-learn.py` 加一个 `--api` 模式，暴露出 POST 接口\n2. 在 task_orchestrator skill 的 SKILL.md 里注册 `wiki_ingest` tool\n3. 把 scene-classifier (3104) 修好，让 hooks 系统能正常工作\n\n**第二优先级：cron 自动化**\n\n```\n# 每小时增量\n0 * * * * /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/wiki-auto-learn.py --mode=ingest --limit=3\n\n# 每日 Lint\n0 3 * * * /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/auto-lint.sh\n```\n\n---\n\n### 真实问题\n\n你之前的问题是**每个组件都想独立跑**，没形成 pipeline：\n- skills/ 变了 → 没人知道\n- entity 该更新 → 没有触发\n- Lint 结果 → 没有闭环\n\n所以现在需要的是**让 trigger 流动起来**。你觉得哪个方向更顺手：\n1. **修好 3104，让 hooks 先工作，再接 wiki-ingest**\n2. **直接加 cron，先让实体页自动化跑起来**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":887,"cacheRead":120242,"cacheWrite":7179,"totalTokens":128362,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0010643999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0072145199999999994,"cacheWrite":0.002692125,"total":0.010987245}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776022481111,"responseId":"062b26d11064e8fd166d5cc9d47d16b6"}}
