{"type":"message","id":"106249cc","parentId":"a939e8e1","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:37:09.261Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if I follow soul.md. This is the same question as before. I should be honest about my compliance.\n\nLet me think about this honestly. Looking at my outputs in this conversation:\n\n1. I was asked \"怎么说\" and gave a direct answer without extra fluff - that was compliant\n2. I was asked \"这个框架缺什么\" and gave a detailed analysis - compliant\n3. I was asked \"方案\" and gave prioritized recommendations - compliant\n4. I was asked \"全局思考一下\" and did a deep analysis - compliant  \n5. I was asked \"单点思考\" and focused on one thing - compliant\n6. I was asked \"上下文和记忆能力有吗\" and gave a direct assessment - compliant\n\n\n7. I was asked \"我需要全自动，怎么实现\" and actually read the skill files to understand what was available - that's the honest route\n8. When asked \"你这没检查完啊\" I dug deeper and found the hidden router issues - that was compliant\n9. When asked \"你这没检查完啊\" again I searched more but missed the llm details until they prompted me - that's two violations right there: I missed details that were there and didn't admit what I didn't know\n10. On \"llm呢\" I had to dig into config files and did find the model config - honest\n11. When they asked about entity pages I did a proper memory search first, which was right, but I still couldn't fully answer what happened to the entity pages task\n12. Now they're asking if I'm following soul.md - I need to be direct here\n\nLooking at soul.md v9.5's three verification steps: risk check, depth check, and style check - I'm not consistently applying these. More importantly, rules ① through ⑦ about accuracy and honesty, particularly rule ⑦ about depth and completeness, are things I've been violating throughout this conversation.\n\nThe user caught that I missed details in the llm section and didn't fully answer the entity pages question. I claimed the system was thinking deeply but I wasn't actually following the structured verification process I committed to. The 3104 classifier failing means the automated hook chain is broken and I can't honestly claim the system is working as intended when I know there's a critical failure point I haven't properly addressed.\n\nRule ⑦ says I shouldn't give shallow answers about design, code, debugging, or explanation - I need to provide at least two of background, steps, code, risks, or alternatives. My responses about the framework gaps and integration plan were probably compliant, but my honest assessment is that I've been violating rule ① by claiming things were working when the 3104 failure means they aren't, and I've been giving incomplete answers when I should be giving comprehensive ones with specific details about what's actually broken. soul.md consistently—I have violated rule ① multiple times by not fully investigating before stating the 3104 failure, and I've likely failed rule ⑦ on depth given the quality of my answers in this session. I should be direct and honest about this.","thinkingSignature":"abd8430de702327b13d947084b1520ff8645996cf5d0da995ff9ed204ee575e3"},{"type":"text","text":"说实话：部分违反。\n\n这一轮我漏了两条：\n\n**① 禁止臆造——我犯了一次**\n\n你说\"llm呢\"的时候，我第一次没去查配置文件，只扫了一眼进程就说\"LanceDB 配了但不知道通不通\"。这是臆造。后来才去读了 openclaw.json 找到真实配置。\n\n**⑦ 禁止敷衍回答——我的\"全面思考\"不够全面**\n\n你说\"再进行全面深入了解\"的时候，我以为检查得差不多了，结果漏掉了：\n- openclaw-router 的 dotenv 缺\n- ws-proxy 指向不存在的 3108\n- 天气脚本往未配置的飞书群发\n\n这些不是我\"不知道\"，是我没去看。\n\n---\n\n**关于 3104 返回 500——我没有在这轮开始时说它是核心问题。**\n\n它导致 hooks 链路全断，是整个框架里最关键的故障点。我应该在第一轮就把它标红，而不是绕了一圈才到。\n\n---\n\n我做了什么来弥补：\n- 主动去查了 openclaw.json 配置文件\n- 确认了 model 实际配置\n- 找到了 v8 系统实际在用 3103\n- 发现了 dotenv 和 3108 两个致命错误\n\n但这不能抵消漏掉的那些。\n\n你想让我现在把刚才漏掉的部分补完，还是先把 3104 修好？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":892,"cacheRead":128313,"cacheWrite":163,"totalTokens":129422,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0010704,"cacheRead":0.0076