{"type":"message","id":"cc1170fa","parentId":"d8e2d46f","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:39:39.950Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants another thorough deep check/inspection. Let me think about what I've checked and what I might have missed.\n\nWhat I know:\n1. Running services (ports, processes)\n2. Cron jobs\n3. Config files (openclaw.json)\n4. Some logs\n5. Scripts\n6. Skills\n\nWhat I might have missed:\n- The actual state of LanceDB vector memory (is it working?)\n- The actual state of the Feishu integration (configured but is it working?)\n- The self-improvement skill actual state\n- The proactivity skill\n- The v8 scoring engine - does it actually receive tasks?\n\n\n- Whether ws-proxy is truly dead or just failing to connect\n- If there's a health check script running that I'm not aware of\n- The actual memory usage and what's stored in entities\n- How the task orchestrator skill is configured\n- Whether the v8 context-protector is functioning\n- What other background processes might be running outside of cron\n\nI need to dig deeper into these areas to get a complete picture.\n\nLooking at the services running, I'm seeing the context API, v8 engine, scene classifier, and gateway all active. The router and ws-proxy are down due to the dotenv issue and wrong port configuration. The weather script appears to be cron-scheduled but likely failing. The health check and memory keeper are available but not currently running, along with the auto-lint and wiki-auto-learn scripts. I should verify the actual state of LanceDB embeddings, whether the Feishu integration is truly operational, and check if there are any hidden running processes outside of cron. Most critically, I need to determine if the gateway is still directly calling the classifier despite the 500 errors, and whether v8's actual scoring logic is working properly. I need to check LanceDB directly to verify if the bge-m3 embeddings are actually functioning, look for any running processes outside of cron, examine the health check logs, and inspect the v8 system's configuration files to see what's actually set up there.","thinkingSignature":"fdb90f24198c62c79044e574e8fe34cfe6b1381e520961623d24e9d730ab5dc4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rvhty4h7bz2m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3104/health 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; curl -s http://localhost:3104/stats 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; ls /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/scene-classifier/logs/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; ls /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/logs/ 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rvhty4h7bz2m_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /home/ai/.openclaw/memory/lancedb/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; du -sh /home/ai/.openclaw/memory/lancedb/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3104/classify -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"你好\"}' 2>/dev/null; echo \"---classify---\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rvhty4h7bz2m_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/scene-classifier/logs/*.log 2>/dev/null | tail -20; echo \"---workspace logs---\"; cat /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/scene-classifier/logs/*.log 2>/dev/null | tail -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":721,"cacheRead":129373,"cacheWrite":684,"totalTokens":130832,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0008652,"cacheRead":0.007762379999999999,"cacheWrite":0.0002565,"total":0.008900279999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776022764263,"responseId":"062b27ebb562a05d411269dd446cdd7d"}}
