{"type":"message","id":"fa112e49","parentId":"967fcf6f","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:39:54.294Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Key finding:\n1. LanceDB IS working - memories.lance file exists, 44K\n2. The scene-classifier logs show:\n   - `Using rule-based fallback classifier: sentence-transformers not installed` - the ML model isn't installed, it's using rule-based fallback\n   - Pipeline initialized successfully\n   - Multiple successful /classify calls (200 OK)\n   - Then: \"Shutting down\" - the process was killed\n3. The classifier API returned 200 for most calls but the actual classify endpoint returned 500 for the Chinese text \"你好\"\n\nWait, the log shows:\n- The working directory scene-classifier (workspace/skills/scene-classifier) initialized with rule-based fallback\n\n\n- Multiple successful classify calls on port 3104\n- Then a shutdown\n\nBut then when I tested with `curl -X POST http://localhost:3104/classify -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"你好\"}'` it returned 500 Internal Server Error.\n\nYet the /health endpoint returns `{\"status\":\"ok\",\"pipeline_loaded\":true,\"circuit_breaker\":{\"is_open\":false,\"failures\":0}` which shows the pipeline is loaded and the circuit breaker is closed. The stats endpoint just returns a message to check logs. So the service was running fine based on the logs, but the current request failed with a 500 error. Let me check what's actually happening with the classify endpoint.\n\nThe scene-classifier is running on 3104 using a rule-based fallback since sentence-transformers isn't installed, the LanceDB memories database is active with 44K of data, and the /classify endpoint was returning 200 OK in the logs before it shut down. But it's returning 500 now when I test it. The process is running as PID 299508 with the API server, so it's the same instance that was generating those successful logs. Something changed between when those logs were written and now.\n\nLooking at the other services, I'm seeing that the context API on 3101 is empty, the v8 engine on 3103 is working fine, the gateway on 18789 appears to be running but the health endpoint isn't responding to my queries, and the router on 3102 is actually the gateway itself which is fine. Let me dig into what's actually failing here.","thinkingSignature":"77b4a634d78140d615a5ae464029adc42c6ba21987ecbf969f8831a2bfd61a5e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jo24gnkfms6i_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:18789/health 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; curl -s http://127.0.0.1:18789/health 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; ss -tlnp | grep 18789"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jo24gnkfms6i_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3104/classify -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"text\":\"你好\"}' -v 2>&1 | tail -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jo24gnkfms6i_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/scene-classifier/logs/api.log 2>/dev/null | tail -10; echo \"---\"; cat /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/skills/scene-classifier/logs/classifier.log 2>/dev/null | tail -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":113234,"output":694,"cacheRead":18037,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131965,"cost":{"input":0.0339702,"output":0.0008328,"cacheRead":0.0010822199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.03588522}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776022780184,"responseId":"062b27fb06f0ed196d81b633214477d9"}}
