{"type":"message","id":"190db5d8","parentId":"3641a379","timestamp":"2026-04-12T19:40:05.215Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The classifier is returning 500 for that specific input. The log from before shows that the classifier WAS working (200 OK for multiple calls), and then the process shut down. The current process (PID 299508) is the same Python API server, but the log file shows \"Shutting down\" which means the log file we're seeing is from an older run.\n\nWait, the log file says:\n```\nINFO:     Application startup complete.\nINFO:     Uvicorn running on http://0.0.0.0:3104\nUsing rule-based fallback classifier: sentence-transformers not installed\nPipeline initialized\n```\n\nThese are startup messages, then shutdown messages. \n\nSo this is from an older run. The current process (299508) must have started fresh and written to a new log file, but the workspace/skills/scene-classifier/logs directory might have rotated or we're looking at stale output. PID 299508 is actually the scene-classifier API server, not the context-api. The context-api running on PID 432 is separate, and the v8 engine is on PID 599. So when I queried localhost:18789 with curl, there was no response, and ss shows port 18789 is listening.\n\nThe issue is that curl is timing out trying to reach the gateway at localhost:18789, but the openclaw-router service that should be forwarding HTTP requests there isn't running due to the dotenv module failure. So port 18789 itself is listening but unreachable through the router.","thinkingSignature":"f9276f5086eb8b55fdb8f5cbe8b952c48f8bbf083ae276d35a8d469e4c6d4599"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2e8i3if33huf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp | grep 18789; echo \"---\"; curl -s --max-time 3 http://127.0.0.1:18789/ 2>&1 | head -5; echo \"---\"; curl -s --max-time 3 http://localhost:18789/ 2>&1 | head -5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2e8i3if33huf_2","name":"exec","argument